Capstone Project on Credit Card Scoring¶

Aim: Predict which customers are good or bad.

Good repay within 89 days (Category 0,1,2,C,X) Bad repay after 90 days (Category 3,4,5)

Source: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/rikdifos/credit-card-approval-prediction

# Remove Outliers for Children Column

print(app_df.CNT_CHILDREN.value_counts())


q1 = app_df.CNT_CHILDREN.quantile(0.25)
q3 = app_df.CNT_CHILDREN.quantile(0.75)

iqr = q3 - q1
upper_bound = q3 +(1.5 * iqr)

print(upper_bound)  #remove rows with more than 5 children

In [134]:
#train test split (train : test is 70% : 30%)
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

X_all_train,X_all_test,y_all_train,y_all_test = train_test_split(X_all,y_all,test_size=0.3,random_state=1)


#Scale the data
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
scaler = StandardScaler()
X_all_train = scaler.fit_transform(X_all_train)
X_all_test = scaler.transform(X_all_test)


# Fit a logistic regression model on test and store the class predictions.
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression   

logreg = LogisticRegression()

logreg.fit(X_all_train,y_all_train)
